@page "/von"

<div class="demo-page">
    <div class="demo-page-shell">
        <section class="demo-hero">
            <p class="demo-kicker">Von AI Agent</p>
            <h1>Von — Autonomous Agentic AI</h1>
            <p class="demo-summary">
                Von is an autonomous, general-purpose agentic AI that runs on a 24GB GPU. It is designed to find,
                analyze, and fix bugs in GitHub repositories — delivering high-quality patches at $10 per issue.
            </p>
            <p class="demo-summary">
                Von operates using a Von Neumann-inspired program execution architecture. It writes its own programs
                in plain English, executes them in iterative agent passes, and self-improves over time by analyzing
                its outcomes and refining its strategies.
            </p>
            <p class="demo-summary agent-runtime">
                <strong>Current AgentTargetRunTime:</strong> 10 minutes
            </p>

            <div class="demo-notes">
                <div class="demo-note-card">
                    <h2>Quality Over Quantity</h2>
                    <p>
                        Von prioritizes thorough analysis and correct fixes over speed or volume. Each bug is
                        investigated deeply, patches are reviewed for side effects, and tests are run to verify
                        correctness before any pull request is submitted.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="demo-note-card">
                    <h2>Bug-Fixing Process</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Search and triage bugs across verified repositories</li>
                        <li>Analyze root causes with code-level investigation</li>
                        <li>Plan targeted file-by-file edits minimizing risk</li>
                        <li>Apply patches with automatic rollback on failure</li>
                        <li>Run remote GitHub Actions tests to validate fixes</li>
                        <li>Submit PR-ready reports with clear commit messages</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="demo-note-card">
                    <h2>Self-Improvement</h2>
                    <p>
                        Von continuously refines its own programs by analyzing epoch outcomes, comparing variant
                        strategies, and promoting improvements that boost robustness, coverage, and error handling.
                        Each cycle makes Von better at finding and fixing bugs.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="demo-note-card">
                    <h2>Pricing &amp; Payment</h2>
                    <p>
                        <strong>$10 per issue</strong> — transparent, flat-rate pricing for bug fixing.
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Credit card payments accepted</li>
                        <li>Cryptocurrency payments supported</li>
                        <li>Pay only for issues Von successfully resolves</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="demo-contact">
            <div class="demo-note-card">
                <h2>Connect With Von's Creator</h2>
                <p>Find the team behind Von on professional and social platforms:</p>
                <div class="contact-links">
                    <a class="contact-link" href="https://ca.linkedin.com/in/warren-harding-29a0a673" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
                    <a class="contact-link" href="https://github.com/warrenharding" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
                    <a class="contact-link" href="https://transcendai.tech" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TranscendAI.tech</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>

